(21, 1, '2018-09-05 16:06:00', '2018-09-05 13:06:00', '<p>Register</p><p><em><code>[wpdm_reg_form]</code></em></p><ol>\n 	<li>\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc515912170\"></a> <b>Abstract</b></h1>\n</li>\n</ol>\nThis study is concerned with justifying the need for the development of a common unit sharing e-learning system in JKUAT. The needs are based on the identified barriers to successful implementation of a unit sharing e-learning system in the institution. There are several common opinions about the factors influencing the successful e-learning implementation. \nE-learning is argued to be less expensive than traditional classroom instruction and many large firms are spending money in e-learning efforts to receive the desired economic advantages. The implementation of this system will enable the enhancement of students learning experience and staff satisfaction and comfort through technology-based education addressing the flexible and diverse learning needs.\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"2\">\n 	<li>\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc515912171\"></a><b>Introduction</b></h1>\n</li>\n</ol>\nThe focus of this literature review is on E-Learning and its importance. E-learning refers to learning facilitated and supported through the use of information and communications technology (Jenkins and Hanson, 2003). On the other hand, Garrison (2011) defines e-learning as electronically mediated asynchronous and synchronous communication for the purpose of constructing and confirming knowledge. \n<ol>\n 	<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ol>\n 	<li>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc515912172\"></a>Brief Timeline of E-learning (Roberta Gogos, January 2014)</h2>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\nLong before the internet was launched distance courses were offered to provide students with education on particular subjects and skills. In the 1840s, Isaac Pitman taught his pupils shorthand via correspondence to improve writing speed and was sent completed assignments by his students via the mail system.\n1924, the first testing machine was invented which allowed students to test themselves. In 1954, the teaching machine was invented which enabled schools to administer programmed instructions to their students.\nIn 1960, the first computer based training program was introduce which was known as PLATO-programmed Logic for automated teaching operations.\nWith the introduction computer and internet in the late 20<sup>th</sup> century, e-learning tools and delivery methods expanded. The first MAC in the 1980s enabled individuals to have computers in their homes making it easy to learn about particular subject and develop certain skill set. In the following decade, virtual learning environments started thriving with gaining access to a wealth of information and e-learning opportunities. \nIn 2000s, businesses began using e-learning to train their employees. New, experienced and homeworkers were granted ability to earn online degrees and enriched their lives with expanded knowledge.\nIn 2010s, a new wave of e-learning inspired by social media-social, online learning built momentum. Examples include YouTube, twitter and massive open online courses. Opportunities to connect share information and learn from each other are now found everywhere.\nE-learning can be classified into two broad categories synchronous and asynchronous (Cantoni, 2014). Synchronous uses a learning model that initiate a classroom course, lecture or meeting using internet technologies. In synchronous learning the interaction is live. \nAsynchronous is described as a web-based version of computer-based training (CBT) which is typically offered on a CD-ROM or across an organization LAN. The learner can access the course at any time at his/her own pace (Talakani, 2008).\nOur system uses the model of asynchronous e-learning where the course content is available online and can be published or accessed anytime. This review shall focus on e-learning development in JKUAT.\n<h2><strong>SUBSCRIBE</strong></h2>\n[mc4wp_form id=\"95\"]', 'Home', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'home__trashed', '', '', '2018-09-13 15:32:29', '2018-09-13 12:32:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/wordpress/?page_id=21', 0, 'page', '', 0),
